               <p>RICHARD CASTLE. I am a <rs id="t18271025-106-viclabel627" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271025-106-victim571 t18271025-106-viclabel627"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18271025-106-crimeloc628">Broad-court, Long-acre</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18271025-106-crimeloc628" type="placeName" value="Broad-court, Long-acre"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18271025-106-crimeloc628" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271025-106-off625 t18271025-106-crimeloc628"></join>. On the 3d of October, about nine o'clock at night, the window of my shop was lifted up, and this bacon taken out; I heard an alarm; the watchman brought the prisoner in; Vaughan said he had stolen the bacon - he did not deny it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271025-106-person572">
                  THOMAS 
                  VAUGHAN
               <interp inst="t18271025-106-person572" type="surname" value="VAUGHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271025-106-person572" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271025-106-person572" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner go and take the bacon from the window; an alarm was given, and he was taken immediately; a boy name Howe tried to take it first; the prisoner then went, and did take it, and threw it to Howe, who let it fall at his feet, and I took it up.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271025-106-person573">
                  ROBERT 
                  CLEGG
               <interp inst="t18271025-106-person573" type="surname" value="CLEGG"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271025-106-person573" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271025-106-person573" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman, and took the prisoner as he came out of the court.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I stood in the court, but saw nothing about it; the gentleman took me, and was going to let me go - I did not take it.</p>
               <p>
